<p>
    <strong>From the college:</strong>
    <i>Mercy College recognizes college-level courses taken by student while still in high school. Advanced Placement (AP) examination score of 3,4, or 5 will normally earn college credit for corresponding courses.</i>
    <br/>
    For more information, <a href="https://www.mercy.edu/admissions/undergraduate-admissions/faq/advising-and-registration/" target="_blank" title="Opens a new window">view the credit policy on this college's website</a>.
